#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Sukhindriyavagga"
msgstr "4. The Pleasure Faculty"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Uppaṭipāṭikasutta → uppatika (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Uppaṭipāṭikasutta"
msgstr "40. Irregular Order"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.40:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.3"
msgid ""
"Dukkhindriyaṃ, domanassindriyaṃ, sukhindriyaṃ, somanassindriyaṃ, "
"upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of pain, sadness, pleasure, happiness, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato "
"uppajjati dukkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of "
"pain arises."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

# Compare AN 2.77-81.
msgctxt "sn48.40:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ, tañca kho sanimittaṃ sanidānaṃ "
"sasaṅkhāraṃ sappaccayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘The faculty of pain has arisen in me. And that has a precursor, a source, a "
"condition, and a reason."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.7"
msgid ""
"Tañca animittaṃ anidānaṃ asaṅkhāraṃ appaccayaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ uppajjissatī’ti—"
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s not possible for the faculty of pain to arise without a precursor, a "
"source, a condition, or a reason.’"

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.8"
msgid ""
"So dukkhindriyañca pajānāti, dukkhindriyasamudayañca pajānāti, "
"dukkhindriyanirodhañca pajānāti, yattha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ "
"nirujjhati tañca pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand the faculty of pain, its origin, its cessation, and where "
"that faculty of pain that’s arisen ceases without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.9"
msgid "Kattha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati?"
msgstr ""
"And where does that faculty of pain that’s arisen cease without anything "
"left over?"

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.10"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.11"
msgid "ettha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"That’s where the faculty of pain that’s arisen ceases without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.12"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aññāsi dukkhindriyassa nirodhaṃ, "
"tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati’."
msgstr ""
"They’re called a mendicant who understands the cessation of the faculty of "
"pain, and who applies their mind to that end."

